Subject: MDKSA-2003:069 - Updated BitchX packages fix DoS vulnerability


-----BEGIN PGP SIGNED MESSAGE-----
Hash: SHA1

________________________________________________________________________

                Mandrake Linux Security Update Advisory
________________________________________________________________________

Package name:           BitchX
Advisory ID:            MDKSA-2003:069
Date:                   June 17th, 2003

Affected versions:	9.0, 9.1
________________________________________________________________________

Problem Description:

 A Denial Of Service (DoS) vulnerability was discovered in BitchX that
 would allow a remote attacker to crash BitchX by changing certain
 channel modes.  This vulnerability has been fixed in CVS and patched
 in the released updates.
________________________________________________________________________

References:
  
  http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CAN-2003-0334
  http://marc.theaimsgroup.com/?l=bugtraq&m=104766521328322&w=2
  http://www.securityfocus.com/archive/1/321093
________________________________________________________________________

